President Obama has nominated Justice Lisabeth Tabor Hughes to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit. Justice Hughes has a long and impressive record of service and has been a Justice on the Kentucky Supreme Court since 2007. She has had a distinguished career as both a jurist and in private practice, handling business and commercial litigation. Justice Hughes has been recognized for her work, being named the Judge of the Year by the Louisville Bar Association in 2012. She is an active member of the legal community and has served on various committees and boards.